1.begin{align*}
\frac{\sqrt{2x}}{\sqrt{3x-1}} &= \frac{3}{2}
\end{align*}

2 corners, we square both sides to eliminate the square roots:
\begin{align*}
\left(\frac{\sqrt{2x}}{\sqrt{3x-1}}\right)^2 &= \left(\frac{3}{2}\right)^2
\end{align*}
\begin{align*}
\frac{2x}{3x-1} &= \frac{9}{4}
\end{align*}

3. To eliminate the fraction, cross-multiply:
\begin{align*}
4 \cdot 2x &= 9 \cdot (3x - 1)
\end{align*}
\begin{align*}
8x &= 27x - 9
\end{align*}

4. Move all terms involving \(x\) to one side of the equation:
\begin{align*}
8x - 27x &= -9
\end{align*}
\begin{align*}
-19x &= -9
\end{align*}

5. Solve for  \(x\) by dividing both sides by \(-19\):
\begin{align*}
x &= \frac{-9}{-19}
\end{align*}
\begin{align*}
x &= \frac{9}{19}
\end{align*}

6. Verify the solution by substituting \(x = \frac{9}{19}\) back into the original equation:
\begin{align*}
\frac{\sqrt{2 \cdot \frac{9}{19}}}{\sqrt{3 \cdot \frac{9}{19} - 1}} &= \frac{\sqrt{\frac{18}{19}}}{\sqrt{\frac{27}{19} - \frac{19}{19}}} = \frac{\sqrt{\frac{18}{19}}}{\sqrt{\frac{8}{19}}} = \frac{\sqrt{18}}{\sqrt{8}} = \frac{3\sqrt{2}}{2\sqrt{2}} = \frac{3}{2}
\end{align*}

The solution satisfies the original equation.

The final answer is \(\boxed{x = \frac{9}{19}}

